---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Live Dashboard - Real-Time Overview - GonoPBX" description="GonoPBX live dashboard: Asterisk status, registered endpoints, active lines, and recent calls updated in real time via WebSocket." lang="en">

  
  <nav class="nav">
    <div class="container">
      <a href="/en/dashboard" class="nav-logo">
        <img src="/logo.png" alt="GonoPBX Logo" />
      </a>
      <button class="nav-toggle" id="navToggle" aria-label="Menu">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
          <path d="M3 12h18M3 6h18M3 18h18" />
        </svg>
      </button>
      <ul class="nav-links" id="navLinks">
        <li><a href="/en/#features">Features</a></li>
        <li><a href="/en/#screenshots">Screenshots</a></li>
        <li><a href="/en/#techstack">Technology</a></li>
        <li><a href="/en/release-notes">Release Notes</a></li>
        <li><a href="/en/blog/">Blog</a></li>
        <li><a href="/en/kontakt">Contact</a></li>
        <li><a href="/en/unterstuetzen">Support</a></li>
        <li class="nav-lang">
          <a href="/dashboard" class="lang-link">DE</a>
          <span class="lang-sep">|</span>
          <a href="/en/dashboard" class="lang-link active">EN</a>
        </li>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/ankaios76/gonopbx" class="nav-cta">GitHub</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </nav>


  <section class="blog-article">
    <div class="container">
      <a href="/en/#features" class="blog-back-link">
        <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M19 12H5"/><path d="M12 19l-7-7 7-7"/></svg>
        Back to overview
      </a>

      <div class="blog-article-header">
        <div class="blog-card-meta" style="justify-content:center;">
          <span class="blog-card-tag">Feature</span>
          <span>Core capability</span>
        </div>
        <h1>Live Dashboard – Everything at a Glance</h1>
      </div>

      <div class="blog-article-content">
        <p>
          The dashboard is the <strong>first page after login</strong>.
          It shows system status, registered endpoints, active lines,
          and recent calls – all updated in real time via WebSocket.
        </p>

        <h2>Features</h2>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>Personal greeting</strong> – Welcome message with username and time</li>
          <li><strong>System status</strong> – Asterisk version, uptime, and connection status</li>
          <li><strong>Endpoints</strong> – All extensions with registration status (online/offline)</li>
          <li><strong>Active lines</strong> – Trunks with registration status at the provider</li>
          <li><strong>Recent calls</strong> – Latest inbound and outbound calls with status</li>
          <li><strong>WebSocket updates</strong> – Live updates without page reload</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Screenshot</h2>

        <div style="margin:32px 0;">
          <img src="/feature-dashboard.png" alt="Live dashboard in GonoPBX" style="width:100%;border-radius:12px;box-shadow:0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);" />
          <p style="text-align:center;color:#718096;font-size:0.9rem;margin-top:8px;">Dashboard with system status, endpoints, and recent calls</p>
        </div>

        <h2>How does it work technically?</h2>

        <p>
          The dashboard uses a <strong>WebSocket connection</strong> to the backend.
          The backend listens to AMI events (Asterisk Manager Interface) and
          pushes changes instantly to all connected clients.
        </p>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>WebSocket</strong> – Bidirectional real-time communication</li>
          <li><strong>AMI events</strong> – PeerStatus, Newchannel, Hangup, and more</li>
          <li><strong>No polling</strong> – Updates arrive instantly, not on timers</li>
          <li><strong>Authenticated</strong> – WebSocket uses JWT tokens as query parameters</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="blog-info-box">
          <p>
            <strong>Available since the first release.</strong>
            The dashboard was expanded with live WebSocket updates in v1.2.0.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <footer class="footer">
    <div class="container">
      <ul class="footer-links">
        <li><a href="https://github.com/ankaios76/gonopbx">GitHub</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://demo.gonopbx.de">Live Demo</a></li>
        <li><a href="/en/unterstuetzen">Support</a></li>
        <li><a href="/impressum">Imprint</a></li>
        <li><a href="/datenschutz">Privacy</a></li>
      </ul>
      <p>&copy; 2026 Norbert Hengsteler. All rights reserved.</p>
    </div>
  </footer>


  <script>
    document.getElementById('navToggle')?.addEventListener('click', () => {
      document.getElementById('navLinks')?.classList.toggle('open');
    });
    document.querySelectorAll('.nav-links a').forEach(link => {
      link.addEventListener('click', () => {
        document.getElementById('navLinks')?.classList.remove('open');
      });
    });
  </script>

</Layout>
